<br>
Ranger pulls with Snare.  A Telekin (stun) followed with a Markar's Discord ('nother stun) puts aggro solidly on me.  Fire a Xuzl and away we go!  <br>
<br>
I run in a large enough circle not to get hit, small enough to avoid aggro on anything else in the area.  Rangergirl (Hi, Teg!) stands back and opens up with EQ/AM3.  I stay ahead of the target, tossing the occasional Agnarr over my shoulder to keep the mob's focus where it belongs.  <br>
<br>
Clean kills, no damage taken, about a bubble of mana per XP message.  If I Harvest when it's up and sit while the ranger heads off for the next one, I usually medd back the mana between pulls so it's constant until the ranger's Range Attack finger needs a break.<br>
<br>
Rhian DeDanaan<br>
64th Wizard<br>
