<br>
roots though are awesome.  greater fetter often lasts the entire time in my experience, provided that you can stop the non-tank melees from trying to TM the mob.  also, a lot of people think that their root isn't lasting just because they see the message that it wore off.  all of the high level roots that different classes get will overwrite each other, so if you get the worn off message, it could just be that someone else cast their root, not realizing that the problem was taken care of. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=492380" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://filebox.vt.edu/users/jomarti8/signature.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimstafftheurgist>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 8258<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 6:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards when they don't Nuke 101</span><hr size=1> Stuns generate aggro, but the aggro created is easily cancelled with a Concussion.  The concept I have is that damage plus a few seconds of standing around not attacking is pretty useful for the melee.  The monster cannot respond and thus proc/cast/move and that's pretty useful at times.  While the savings in damage from heal isn't enormous, the savings in lack of attacks and abilities can be valuable to the group for not a lot of mana.<br>
<br>
Stuns are more useful than most people give them credit for, and not just for stopping gaters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jadrax>Jadrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1466<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 6:36 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards when they don't Nuke 101</span><hr size=1> With a long duration stun the main tank should easily have time to get agro back off you while the mobs not doing anything. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=natanmagus>Natan Magus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1074<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 6:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> Stuns are really not that usefull in the higher tier PoP zones - even IF (and that is a big 'if') the Mobs should be actually affected by it.<br>
<br>
The higher you level, the more you get access to the higher tier zones the less our 'utility' spells are 'usefull'. (That's my very personal opinion.)<br>
In the level range of 40 up to zones like PoN maybe, there is an use for it (especially for stuns) and it is efficient maybe even too. But once you surpassed that mark it gets less and less efficient. (Keep in mind that all of our lower stuns spells will have absolutely no impact on those Mobs.)<br>
Clerics and Paladins take over the stun role now and to be honest... i am not sad about that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimstafftheurgist>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 8259<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 7:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POP goes the stun</span><hr size=1> Right, utility varies a lot based on level, location, and group composition.  I've always noted I'm more use to a group the fewer other casters there are because I can provide more than just a blast (at least that's what it feels like).  Not that the blasts are no good, just it feels more useful to do other stuff.  I'm running into more and more monsters I just can't stun any more and its frustrating.  Further, the higher level you get, the more specialized classes get, so the &quot;toss in a little help&quot; classes like Bards and Druids - or our utility - is less noticable or even useful.<br>
